Class Crocodile

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
gameObject.GameObject
gameObject.MovableObject
gameObject.object.Crocodile
All Implemented Interfaces:
Actable, Movable, javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class Crocodile
extends MovableObject
Crocodile in the game scene.

When Animal hits on BigTrunk in game scene, if it doesn't open its mouth, Animal could stand on it safely. If it opens its mouth, Animal would die if standing on it.

  • Constructor Details

    • Crocodile

      public Crocodile​(int xpos, int ypos, int w, int h, double speed)
      Creates a Crocodile.

      It sets the image of the crocodile, sets its own action type and sets the speed of the crocodile.

      Parameters:
      xpos - x coordinate of the crocodile
      ypos - y coordinate of the crocodile
      w - width of the crocodile
      h - height of the crocodile
      speed - speed of the crocodile

  • Method Details

    • act

      public void act​(long now)
      The action that Crocodile does in current frame.

      It swims in the river horizontally. It opens its mouth for 1s in every 6s.

      Parameters:
      now - the current time

    • setCrocodileImage

      public void setCrocodileImage​(long now)
      Set the images of Crocodile based on the current time.

      It opens its mouth for 1s in every 7s and closes its moth for 6s in every 7s.

      Parameters:
      now - the current time
